iguration object for a ‘SBSDKBaseScannerViewController’ and its subclasses.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Sometimes it is necessary to limit a live video frame detection or recognition to a certain rectangular area with","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"a specific aspect ratio: the region or rectangle of interest. This is where a view finder comes in.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"It crops the video frame to that region of interest before passing it to any scanner. Usually","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the performance of scanners gain a benefit from it because less pixels must be processed.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Additionally, to guide the user, the view finder visualizes the region of interest by drawing a rectangle around","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"on the user interface.","type":"text"}]},"doc://net.doo.ScanbotSDK/documentation/ScanbotSDK/SBSDKBaseScannerViewFinderConfiguration/style":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The drawing style of the finder view."}],"url":"\/documentation\/scanbotsdk\/sbsdkbasescannerviewfinderconfiguration\/style","kind":"symbol","title":"style","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"style"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"SBSDKFinderView","preciseIdentifier":"c:@M@ScanbotSDK@objc(cs)SBSDKFinderView"},{"kind":"text","text":"."},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Style","preciseIdentifier":"s:10ScanbotSDK15SBSDKFinderViewC5StyleO"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"style"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/net.doo.ScanbotSDK\/documentation\/ScanbotSDK\/SBSDKBaseScannerViewFinderConfiguration\/style","type":"topic"}},"variantOverrides":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}],"patch":[{"value":"occ","op":"replace","path":"\/identifier\/interfaceLanguage"},{"value":"Instance Property","op":"replac